sentences: Tyler Smith (born August 9, 1986), also known by his nickname Telle, is an American musician and songwriter.
Smith joined In Fear and Faith as one of their two lead vocalists in May 2007 to replace founding vocalist Jarred DeArmas.

Smith performed on the band's debut release Voyage and was a member of the band until January 2008 (a month after the release of the EP), when he joined Phoenix, Arizona-based Greeley Estates as bassist.
He left the band on November 14, 2008, the day before the band was about to go on tour with Alesana.
Upon his departure, he joined the Word Alive, originally a side-project by former Blessthefall and Escape the Fate's Craig Mabbitt, on December 3, 2008.
On January 20, 2010, he stated it would be titled Deceiver.
Deceiver was released on August 31, 2010.
In 2010, the Word Alive were included in Underoath's November tour.

On January 24, 2011, while the Word Alive were on tour with Texas in July and For Today, Smith was hospitalized due to an unknown virus and bacterial bronchitis, laryngitis and pharyngitis along with a fever of 103.6 °F.
In 2011, Smith wrote and completed two new songs, "Apologician" and "Lights and Stones", for the deluxe edition of Deceiver, which was released on June 7, 2011.

On March 31, 2012, the Word Alive released a new song by the name of "Wishmaster".
By early 2011, Smith began a clothing line by the name of Resist & Rebel, which he co-operated with Andrew Paiano (Woe, Is Me) until 2013 when Andrew stepped down.

Smith was a member of Greeley Estates from January 2008 to November 2008.
He is currently the lead vocalist of Arizona metalcore band the Word Alive and has played in several bands, such as  Greeley Estates and In Fear and Faith.

Smith performed on the band's debut release Voyage and was a member of the band until January 2008 (a month after the release of the EP), when he joined Phoenix, Arizona-based Greeley Estates as bassist.
He left the band on November 14, 2008, the day before the band was about to go on tour with Alesana.
A year in advance of its release, Smith confirmed the writing of the Word Alive's first studio album.
In 2010, the Word Alive were included in Underoath's November tour.
At the Mission, Texas show, Smith substituted for Underoath vocalist Spencer Chamberlain who had contracted food poisoning during the tour's final week.

On January 24, 2011, while the Word Alive were on tour with Texas in July and For Today, Smith was hospitalized due to an unknown virus and bacterial bronchitis, laryngitis and pharyngitis along with a fever of 103.6 °F.
On that same day, they confirmed the new album Life Cycles would be released on July 3.
The album currently has two singles called "Entirety" and the eponymous "Life Cycles".
Tyler Smith was born in Dayton, Ohio.
